// SUMMARY

  Purpose:    Production-grade Tamil LLM. Powers enterprise agent stack.
              Tolkappiyam-standard. On-premise deployable.

  Architecture: DECODER-ONLY TRANSFORMER, designed for Tamil morphology:
  - **Tokenizer (primary):** Custom Tamil BPE (50K-65K vocab, NOT adapted from English)
  - **Tokenizer (research track):** Swaram-based tokenizer — see SWARAM_VS_TOKEN_RESEARCH.md
  - Vocabulary: 50,000-65,000 tokens (Tamil-optimized, includes compound forms)
  - Context: 4K tokens (longer than typical English models for agglutinative morphology)
  - Embeddings: 1,024-2,048 dim (calibrated for Tamil semantic density)
  - Layers: 12-24 (depending on parameter budget: 100M, 300M, 1B)
  - Attention: Multi-head with Tamil-specific positional encoding

  Pre-training: FROM SCRATCH on Tamil-dominant corpus
  - Seed corpus: OpenSangam (CC-BY Tamil literature, ~505K tokens core)
  - Extended corpus: Modern Tamil (news, govt, literature — Agam-private tier)
  - Synthetic data: Tamil dialogue (CC-BY)
  - Training objective: Causal LM with Tamil span masking
  - Total pre-training tokens: 1B-10B (depending on model size)
  - Hardware: Sovereign cluster (S-Nodes) + opportunistic cloud GPU
  - License: Apache 2.0

  Swaram research track (PARALLEL experiment):
  - See docs/research/SWARAM_VS_TOKEN_RESEARCH.md for full rationale
  - Hypothesis: Swarams (Tamil musical atoms) are better atomic units than BPE tokens
  - Train Adhan-S (swaram tokenizer) alongside Adhan-B (BPE) on identical data
  - Compare empirically in Q1 2027
  - If swaram wins by >=10%: ship Adhan v2 with swaram tokenizer
  - If swaram competitive (within 5%): offer both, swaram for Tamil-first users
  - Connection to Pann isai: Tamil's musical origins (Tolkappiyam, 3rd c. BCE)
  - Connection to token-free research: ByT5 (Google 2021), CANINE (Google 2022)

  Phases (UPDATED Jun 18):
  1. Data collection         ✅ Complete (Sangam + modern + synthetic)
  2. Tamil tokenizer design  🔄 Active (Q3 2026)
  3. Architecture design     🔄 Active (Q3 2026)
  4. From-scratch pre-train  📋 Planned (Q4 2026 - Q1 2027)
  5. Instruction tuning      📋 Planned (Q1 2027)
  6. ONNX quantization       📋 Planned (Q2 2027)
  7. Downstream tasks        📋 Planned (Q2 2027)

  LEGACY (archive as `adhan-gemma-v0.5`):
  - Gemma-fine-tuned model (NOT Tamil-first, transitional only)
  - Deprecate after from-scratch v1.0 ships

  Enterprise use:
  - Bundled with Agam Enterprise node (service/agent/)
  - Local inference, no API fees, DPDP compliant
  - Pricing: ₹10,00,000–₹15,00,000 setup

// RELATIONSHIP
  adhan  →  service/agent/ enterprise stack
